&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stoma Care Nurse Band 6 (37.5 hours)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Stoma Care team at West Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust, are seeking an enthusiastic nurse with experience within surgery, with an interest of colorectal and stoma care. They need to be able to work flexibly and collaboratively in a busy team, working in hospital, outpatients and community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst the successful candidate will be required to work independently in providing education and information, advice and support to pre-op and post-op stoma patients, you will also be required to liaise and work closely with other health care professionals in ensuring that patient care needs are met accordingly and that care is delivered to a high standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate needs to be prepared to undertake their ongoing professional development to ensure that they are competent to fulfil the role. Opportunities will be provided to develop your clinical skills and academic knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills with patients and members of the MDT. Need to have good IT skills and experience in preparing teaching, presenting and audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has the commitment, professionalism and dedication to make a difference to our patients and help the Stoma Care team achieve the Trusts vision of “the very best care for every patient, every day”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paula Bowen-williams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CNS Stoma Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;paula.williams-bowen@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01923 217489&lt;/p&gt;
